abstract: The former vice president’s backers have noted a lack of enthusiasm and a spotty campaign operation as reasons Joe Biden is lagging in Iowa, not to mention a formidable moderate competitor in Pete Buttigieg.
snippet: The former vice president’s backers have noted a lack of enthusiasm and a spotty campaign operation as reasons Joe Biden is lagging in Iowa, not to mention a formidable moderate competitor in Pete Buttigieg.
lead_paragraph: WINTERSET, Iowa — Nancy Courtney displays a Joe Biden sign in her yard, makes phone calls for his campaign and supports the former vice president “100 percent,” she said. But the sluggish state of Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s organization in her city of Burlington, Iowa, had her fuming one recent evening.

abstract: President Trump’s former press secretary has returned to Arkansas a bona fide star eager to play a new role in a post-Trump Republican Party.
snippet: President Trump’s former press secretary has returned to Arkansas a bona fide star eager to play a new role in a post-Trump Republican Party.
lead_paragraph: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. — It has been less than six months since Sarah Huckabee Sanders left Washington after a tumultuous tenure as President Trump’s press secretary who was mocked so mercilessly at the White House Correspondents’ Dinner that other members of the Trump administration walked out.

headline_main: Her Battles With the Press Corps Behind Her, Sanders Plans a Political Future
headline_print_headline: Tiffs With Press Corps Behind Her, Sanders Plans Political Future

abstract: Anxious about the cost of a single-payer health system, more voters now support the idea of a government-run plan that would compete with private insurance.
snippet: Anxious about the cost of a single-payer health system, more voters now support the idea of a government-run plan that would compete with private insurance.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — One after another, voters at a recent campaign event here for former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. expressed utter comfort with the centerpiece of his health care platform: an idea once so controversial that Democrats had to drop it from the Affordable Care Act to get the landmark law passed.

abstract: Mr. Bloomberg brings a huge personal fortune and moderate views to an increasingly fluid race, but issues like criminal justice and his late start loom as vulnerabilities.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg brings a huge personal fortune and moderate views to an increasingly fluid race, but issues like criminal justice and his late start loom as vulnerabilities.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg announced on Sunday that he would run for president in 2020, bringing his enormous wealth and eclectic political biography into the tumultuous Democratic primary and seeking to win over skeptical liberal voters by presenting himself as a multibillion-dollar threat to President Trump.

abstract: All summer, she was soaring, slinging buzzy plans and climbing in the polls. It’s not summer anymore.
snippet: All summer, she was soaring, slinging buzzy plans and climbing in the polls. It’s not summer anymore.
lead_paragraph: VINTON, Iowa — Elizabeth Warren motors onstage at her campaign events like she is being chased: arm-pump, arm-pump, mid-jog wave. O.K.! Let’s get this thing going.

abstract: In the absence of a clear front-runner, some lower-polling candidates were able to break through — at least for one news cycle.
snippet: In the absence of a clear front-runner, some lower-polling candidates were able to break through — at least for one news cycle.
lead_paragraph: It was a busy week in the Democratic presidential campaign, with a flood of new policies and, of course, another debate.

abstract: The story behind the first part of our new series on presidential candidates.
snippet: The story behind the first part of our new series on presidential candidates.
lead_paragraph: Today’s episode kicks off “The Candidates,” a new series from “The Daily” that profiles the four top-polling Democratic presidential contenders: Pete Buttigieg, Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Joe Biden. Producers Clare Toeniskoetter and Luke Vander Ploeg told us about how they approached the first episode:

headline_main: How We Chose a Moment for Pete Buttigieg
byline_original: By Clare Toeniskoetter and Luke Vander Ploeg

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York City and expected presidential candidate, is buying ads in more than two dozen states.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York City and expected presidential candidate, is buying ads in more than two dozen states.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the billionaire former mayor of New York City, spent at least $30 million on Friday for a single week of television ads, a show of financial force that signals his willingness to use his vast personal fortune to reshape the Democratic presidential race.
